Package si.ijs.kt.clus.error

Class BinaryPredictionList

java.lang.Object
si.ijs.kt.clus.error.BinaryPredictionList
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class BinaryPredictionList extends Object implements Serializable
This class could be used in any kind of classification setting (e.g., hierarchical multilabel) and basically stores the statistics, which enables as to compute the number of TP, TN, FP and FN (T - true, F - false, P - positives, and N - negatives) for any given threshold.

The class is used for constructing ROC- and PR-curves, where the threshold vary, hence it basically stores the triplets

(probability(X), truth, count)

where

  • 0.0 <= probability(X) <= 1.0 denotes our estimate of probability of presence of some fixed label X (or positive class),
  • truth = true | false denotes the ground truth, and
  • count denotes the number of examples seen, with the first two properties.

      Parameters:
      actual - Ground truth, denotes the presence of a given label (or belonging to positive class)
      predicted - Ranges between 0 and 1 and gives the estimate of probability that the given example is labelled by the label (or belonging to positive class)
